    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-22T13:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-22T13:36:00-05:00" n="995"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d995">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/241.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-22T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed by the American colony committee that they desire 1,000
                    Krag-Jorgensen rifles at price stated and 250,000 cartridges therefor, to be
                    shipped by Ward Line steamer leaving New York [next Thursday?].</p>
                <p>Attention is called to the fact that the military attaché has no right of entry,
                    and I request instructions as to course resulting therefrom.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
